r (d. 1992)\nBULLET::::- 1910 – Ronald Coase, English-American economist, author, and academic, Nobel Prize laureate (d. 2013)\nBULLET::::- 1911 – Klaus Fuchs, German physicist and spy (d. 1988)\nBULLET::::- 1914 – Zainul Abedin, Bangladeshi painter and academic (d. 1976)\nBULLET::::- 1914 – Billy Tipton, American pianist and saxophonist (d. 1989)\nBULLET::::- 1914 – Albert Tucker, Australian painter and illustrator (d. 1999)\nBULLET::::- 1915 – Bill Osmanski, American football player and coach (d. 1996)\nBULLET::::- 1915 – Robert Ruark, American hunter and author (d. 1965)\nBULLET::::- 1915 – Jo Van Fleet, American actress (d. 1996)\nBULLET::::- 1917 – Tom Bradley, American lieutenant, lawyer, and politician, 38th Mayor of Los Angeles (d. 1998)\nBULLET::::- 1917 – Ramanand Sagar, Indian director and producer (d. 2005)\nBULLET::::- 1919 – Alfred de Grazia, American political scientist and author (d. 2014)\nBULLET::::- 1919 – Roman Vlad, Italian pianist and composer (d. 2013)\nBULLET::::- 1920 – Viveca Lindfors, Swedish-American actress, singer and poet (d. 1995)\nBULLET::::- 1921 – Dobrica Ćosić, Serbian politician, 1st President of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (d. 2014)\nBULLET::::- 1922 – Little Joe Cook, American singer-songwriter (d. 2014)\nBULLET::::- 1922 – William Gaddis, American author and academic (d. 1998)\nBULLET::::- 1923 – Cheikh Anta Diop, Senegalese historian, anthropologist, and physicist (d. 1986)\nBULLET::::- 1923 – Morton Estrin, American pianist and educator (d. 2017)\nBULLET::::- 1923 – Dina Merrill, American actress, game show panelist, socialite, heiress, and businesswoman (d. 2017)\nBULLET::::- 1923 – Shlomo Venezia, Greek-Italian author and Holocaust survivor (d. 2012)\nBULLET::::- 1923 – Yvonne Choquet-Bruhat, French mathematician and physicist\nBULLET::::- 1924 – Joe Allbritton, American businessman and publisher, founded the Allbritton Communications Company (d. 2012)\nBULLET::::- 1924 – Kim Song-ae, Korean politician (d.2014)\nBUL